      "content_html": "<p>India Real Estate Market 2026 ek crucial turning point par hai. Ek taraf record-high property prices hain, doosri taraf foreign investment mein 75% ki giri. To aakhir ho kya raha hai?</p>\n    <h3>Asli Picture Yeh Hai</h3>\n    <p>2025 mein India ka real estate sector ₹595 billion tak pahuncha — global market ka 13.8% hissa. Residential launches 270,000+ units rahe. Luxury segment (₹1.25 Cr+) demand 11% se badh kar 27% ho gayi. Yeh growth ke signals hain.</p>\n    <p>Lekin Q1 2026 ne jhataaka diya. Colliers India ke data ke mutabiq, foreign investment ₹1.6 billion se girakar sirf ₹400 million reh gayi — ek quarter mein 75% crash. Overall institutional investment bhi 60%+ gira.</p>\n    <h3>Toh Kya Yeh Slowdown Hai?</h3>\n    <p>Partly haan, partly nahi. Yeh slowdown geopolitical tension-driven hai — West Asia conflict ne global investors ko cautious bana diya. Lekin India ke fundamentals strong hain. Domestic investors ne gap fill kiya — total investment ka 75% hissa ab Indian investors de rahe hain.</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Office leasing: 55 million sq ft absorption expected 2026</li>\n      <li>Rental growth: 6-8% projected across major cities</li>\n      <li>Home loan rates 7% ke paas — 2022 ke baad lowest</li>\n      <li>Top-8 cities mein residential sales 14% gire in 2025</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Conclusion:</strong> Yeh full slowdown nahi, recalibration hai. Metro cities thak rahi hain. Tier-2 cities abhi shuru ho rahi hain. Market 2031 tak $927 billion reach karega. Long game wale investors ke liye 2026 window of opportunity hai, panic ka time nahi.</p>",
