      "content_html": "<p>Har jagah ek hi sawaal sun rahe hain: \"Bhai, property market down ja raha hai kya?\" Social media par fear, news mein confusion. Aao ground reality samjhein.</p>\n    <p><strong>Short answer:</strong> Partial dip — poora nahi, kuch jagah haan.</p>\n    <h3>Numbers Kya Kehte Hain</h3>\n    <p>Top-8 cities mein residential sales 2024 ke 4.37 lakh units se girakar 2025 mein 3.86 lakh units — 12% decline. Lekin total transaction VALUE 6% badhi. Matlab log kum unit khareed rahe hain, lekin higher-priced properties mein. Yeh panic nahi — yeh selectivity hai.</p>\n    <h3>Kahan Dip, Kahan Nahi</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Dip areas:</strong> Mumbai premium zones, Gurgaon overpriced sectors, Bengaluru fringe areas</li>\n      <li><strong>Stable/Growing:</strong> Hyderabad, Ahmedabad, Tier-2 cities, warehousing segment</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Yeh 2008 Jaisi Crash Kyun Nahi</h3>\n    <p>2008 mein subprime mortgage crisis tha — toxic debt globally. India mein aisa kuch nahi. RERA regulations, strong income verification, no systemic debt exposure. Yeh breathing space hai, collapse nahi.</p>\n    <p><strong>Investor message:</strong> Market dip = better entry point. Jab sab darr rahe hote hain, tab smart buyers position lete hain. The best deals happen when sentiment is cautious.</p>",
