      "content_html": "<p>Mumbai mein ₹2 crore mein 2BHK milti hai. Raipur mein ₹35-45 lakh mein. Same modern amenities, same gated community — alag sirf price tag hai. Aur yahi Tier-2 cities ka story hai.</p>\n    <h3>Kya Ho Raha Hai Tier-2 Mein</h3>\n    <p>Top 30 Tier-2 cities mein property prices 3 saal mein 14% se 65% tak badhe. Jaipur mein 65%, Guntur mein 51%, Mangalore mein 41% appreciation aayi. Aur yeh abhi shuru hai.</p>\n    <h3>Kyun Boom Aa Raha Hai</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Infrastructure investment: NH expansion, metro rail, BRTS, ring roads</li>\n      <li>Job decentralization: IT, BPO, manufacturing Tier-2 shift ho raha hai</li>\n      <li>Affordable housing demand: Middle class ke liye metro unaffordable</li>\n      <li>Smart City projects: Civic infrastructure upgrade</li>\n      <li>NRI interest: Roots wale NRIs ghar wahan khareed rahe hain</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Top Tier-2 Performers 2026</h3>\n    <p>Jaipur (tourism + IT), Indore (IIM + commerce), Nagpur (MIHAN + logistics), <strong>Raipur (most affordable + Naya Raipur)</strong>, Lucknow (government + defense).</p>\n    <p><strong>Bottom line:</strong> Tier-2 cities 2026-2030 mein India ki real estate growth ka engine hone wali hain. Jo aaj entry leta hai woh 5 saal baad Indore-Pune story repeat hote dekhega apni property mein.</p>",
