      "content_html": "<p>₹50 lakh aapke paas hain. Mumbai mein 1BHK loge ya Raipur mein 3BHK? Yeh sirf size ka sawaal nahi — yeh return ka sawaal hai.</p>\n    <h3>Metro Reality Check 2026</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Mumbai:</strong> ₹20,000-45,000/sq ft. Rental yield: 2-3%. Correction risk: High</li>\n      <li><strong>Delhi NCR:</strong> ₹12,000-22,000/sq ft. Inventory pressure. 10-25% correction possible</li>\n      <li><strong>Bengaluru:</strong> Strongest metro, but affordability stretched</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Tier-2 Reality 2026</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Raipur:</strong> ₹3,810/sq ft avg. Rental yield: 4.4-7.1%. Stable appreciation</li>\n      <li><strong>Nagpur:</strong> ₹4,500-7,000/sq ft. MIHAN-backed. Steady demand</li>\n      <li><strong>Indore:</strong> ₹5,500-8,000/sq ft. 20% appreciation. Strong rental market</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>The Math</h3>\n    <p>₹50L metro mein: 2-3% yield + slowing appreciation. ₹50L Tier-2 mein: 4-7% yield + early-stage appreciation curve. Long-term (7-10 year horizon) mein, early-stage Tier-2 consistently metro's stagnant premium zones ko outperform karta hai.</p>\n    <p><strong>Caveat:</strong> Tier-2 mein liquidity kam hoti hai. Exit 5+ saal mein sochna hoga. Always RERA-verified projects chuno.</p>",
