      "description": "RBI ne 2025 mein rates 125 bps cut kiye. Ab repo rate 5.25% par hai. Home loan rates 7% ke paas aa gayi hain — 2022 ke baad lowest. Iska property market par directly kya asar padta hai? Rate Cut = EMI...",
      "content_html": "<p>RBI ne 2025 mein rates 125 bps cut kiye. Ab repo rate 5.25% par hai. Home loan rates 7% ke paas aa gayi hain — 2022 ke baad lowest. Iska property market par directly kya asar padta hai?</p>\n    <h3>Rate Cut = EMI Relief</h3>\n    <p>₹50 lakh ka 20-saal ka loan. 8.5% par EMI: ₹43,391. 7% par EMI: ₹38,765. Monthly fark: ₹4,626. Saal mein ₹55,512 bachte hain. Yeh meaningful relief hai mid-segment buyers ke liye.</p>\n    <h3>Demand Par Asar</h3>\n    <p>Jab rates low hote hain, affordability badhti hai. More buyers qualify karte hain home loans ke liye. Developers ko sales velocity badhti dikhti hai. Unsold inventory absorb hoti hai faster.</p>\n    <h3>But Rate Cut = Auto Boom Nahi Hota</h3>\n    <p>If property prices are already too high (like certain Mumbai or Gurgaon zones), even lower EMIs don't make the deal attractive. Rate cuts help most in mid-segment and Tier-2 markets where price-to-income ratios are still reasonable.</p>\n    <h3>2026 mein Kya Expected Hai</h3>\n    <p>Market consensus — near-term mein rates stable rahenge 7% ke aas paas. Iska matlab hai ab jo buyers fence par hain, unhe enter karna chahiye. Rate cuts ka full benefit mid-2026 se end-users feel karenge.</p>\n    <p><strong>Investor strategy:</strong> Low rate environment mein leveraged investment (loan lekar property lena) samajhdari ho sakti hai — agar rental yield loan rate se higher hai toh positive carry milta hai.</p>",
