      img: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1605276374104-dee2a0ed3cd6?w=600&auto=format&fit=crop&q=60",
      "tags": [
        "Real Estate vs Stocks",
        "Comparison"
      ],
      "description": "India mein yeh debate kabhi khatam nahi hoti. \"Equity better hai!\" vs \"Property safe hai!\" Dono ke fans hain. Lekin data kya kehta hai? Real Estate ke Advantages Tangible asset — zero se sab kuch nahi...",
      "content_html": "<p>India mein yeh debate kabhi khatam nahi hoti. \"Equity better hai!\" vs \"Property safe hai!\" Dono ke fans hain. Lekin data kya kehta hai?</p>\n    <h3>Real Estate ke Advantages</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Tangible asset — zero se sab kuch nahi ho sakta</li>\n      <li>Leverage possible — ₹10L se ₹50L ki property control kar sakte ho</li>\n      <li>Dual return — rent + appreciation</li>\n      <li>Tax benefits — home loan interest deduction</li>\n      <li>Inflation hedge — prices long-term mein badhe hain</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Stock Market ke Advantages</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Liquidity — kisi bhi din sell kar sakte ho</li>\n      <li>Lower entry — SIP ₹500 se shuru</li>\n      <li>No management — property maintenance nahi</li>\n      <li>Diversification easier — 50 companies ek portfolio mein</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Real Comparison (10 Saal)</h3>\n    <p>Sensex returns historically 12-14% CAGR. Real estate (good city, good location): 8-15% appreciation + 4-7% rental yield = 12-22% total. But real estate has illiquidity premium — and higher individual deal variance.</p>\n    <h3>Verdict</h3>\n    <p>Neither is universally better. <strong>Best portfolio = both.</strong> Real estate for stability + rental income. Equity for liquidity + growth. Jis kisi ka sirf ek hi option hai — at least woh option optimize karo.</p>",
      "content_text": "India mein yeh debate kabhi khatam nahi hoti. \"Equity better hai!\" vs \"Property safe hai!\" Dono ke fans hain. Lekin data kya kehta hai? Real Estate ke Advantages Tangible asset — zero se sab kuch nahi ho sakta Leverage possible — ₹10L se ₹50L ki property control kar sakte ho Dual return — rent + appreciation Tax benefits — home loan interest deduction Inflation hedge — prices long-term mein badhe hain Stock Market ke Advantages Liquidity — kisi bhi din sell kar sakte ho Lower entry — SIP ₹500 se shuru No management — property maintenance nahi Diversification easier — 50 companies ek portfolio mein Real Comparison (10 Saal) Sensex returns historically 12-14% CAGR. Real estate (good city, good location): 8-15% appreciation + 4-7% rental yield = 12-22% total. But real estate has illiquidity premium — and higher individual deal variance. Verdict Neither is universally better. Best portfolio = both. Real estate for stability + rental income. Equity for liquidity + growth. Jis kisi ka sirf ek hi option hai — at least woh option optimize karo.",
