      "description": "Itne saare cities hain — kahan invest karein? Data ke basis par 2026 ke top investment cities ki ranked list. Tier-1 (Stable but Entry Difficult) Hyderabad: Strongest metro — tech demand, lower correc...",
      "content_html": "<p>Itne saare cities hain — kahan invest karein? Data ke basis par 2026 ke top investment cities ki ranked list.</p>\n    <h3>Tier-1 (Stable but Entry Difficult)</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Hyderabad:</strong> Strongest metro — tech demand, lower correction risk, 3-4% yield</li>\n      <li><strong>Ahmedabad:</strong> Affordable metro, GIFT City growth, stable appreciation</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Tier-2 Stars (Best Risk-Reward 2026)</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Raipur:</strong> ₹3,810/sq ft, 7.1% max yield, early-stage, Smart City — Best Value Pick 2026</li>\n      <li><strong>Nagpur:</strong> MIHAN backed, logistics hub, BRTS expansion, ₹4,500-7,000/sq ft</li>\n      <li><strong>Indore:</strong> Strong rental market, 20% 3-yr appreciation, commerce hub</li>\n      <li><strong>Jaipur:</strong> Tourism + IT, 65% price jump 2022-25, still room for growth</li>\n      <li><strong>Bhubaneswar:</strong> Smart City, IT growth, 15% appreciation</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Cities to Watch (2027-28 Horizon)</h3>\n    <p>Nashik, Mysuru, Vizag, Coimbatore — next wave Tier-2 cities with strong economic base and undervalued properties.</p>\n    <p><strong>Final call:</strong> Raipur offers the best combination of affordability + yield + early appreciation in 2026. It's where Indore was 5 years ago. Aur Indore ka story aap jaante hain.</p>",
      "content_text": "Itne saare cities hain — kahan invest karein? Data ke basis par 2026 ke top investment cities ki ranked list. Tier-1 (Stable but Entry Difficult) Hyderabad: Strongest metro — tech demand, lower correction risk, 3-4% yield Ahmedabad: Affordable metro, GIFT City growth, stable appreciation Tier-2 Stars (Best Risk-Reward 2026) Raipur: ₹3,810/sq ft, 7.1% max yield, early-stage, Smart City — Best Value Pick 2026 Nagpur: MIHAN backed, logistics hub, BRTS expansion, ₹4,500-7,000/sq ft Indore: Strong rental market, 20% 3-yr appreciation, commerce hub Jaipur: Tourism + IT, 65% price jump 2022-25, still room for growth Bhubaneswar: Smart City, IT growth, 15% appreciation Cities to Watch (2027-28 Horizon) Nashik, Mysuru, Vizag, Coimbatore — next wave Tier-2 cities with strong economic base and undervalued properties. Final call: Raipur offers the best combination of affordability + yield + early appreciation in 2026. It's where Indore was 5 years ago. Aur Indore ka story aap jaante hain.",
