      "content_html": "<p>Madhya Pradesh aur Chhattisgarh ke do prominent cities — Indore aur Raipur. Dono Tier-2, dono growing. Lekin investor ke liye 2026 mein kaun better hai?</p>\n    <h3>Indore: The Established Performer</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Price: ₹5,500-8,000/sq ft</li>\n      <li>3-yr appreciation: ~20%</li>\n      <li>Rental yield: 3.5-5%</li>\n      <li>Drivers: IIM, commerce hub, clean city reputation</li>\n      <li>Status: Mid-stage market — discovery happening</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Raipur: The Early-Stage Opportunity</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Price: ₹3,810/sq ft average (30-40% cheaper than Indore)</li>\n      <li>3-yr appreciation: 14% (stable base, pre-acceleration)</li>\n      <li>Rental yield: 4.4-7.1% (higher than Indore)</li>\n      <li>Drivers: Industry, state capital, Smart City, Naya Raipur</li>\n      <li>Status: Early-stage — best entry point now</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>The Verdict</h3>\n    <p>Indore abhi bhi good investment hai — established, stable, decent returns. But Raipur offers: lower entry price + higher rental yield + earlier appreciation stage = better risk-adjusted return for 5-7 year horizon.</p>\n    <p>Indore ka growth story zyada tar already price mein hai. Raipur ka growth story abhi write ho raha hai. Agar aap early-mover advantage chahte hain — Raipur answer hai.</p>",
