      "description": "Dono Central India ke major Tier-2 cities. Dono infrastructure-backed. Dono affordable vs metros. Lekin ek investor ke liye kaun better choice hai 2026 mein? Nagpur Snapshot Price: ₹4,500-7,000/sq ft ...",
      "content_html": "<p>Dono Central India ke major Tier-2 cities. Dono infrastructure-backed. Dono affordable vs metros. Lekin ek investor ke liye kaun better choice hai 2026 mein?</p>\n    <h3>Nagpur Snapshot</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Price: ₹4,500-7,000/sq ft</li>\n      <li>Key driver: MIHAN (Multi-modal International Cargo Hub and Airport)</li>\n      <li>Metro expansion: Phase 2 underway</li>\n      <li>Appreciation: ~12% in 3 years</li>\n      <li>Strength: Logistics, IT parks, manufacturing — diversified economy</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Raipur Snapshot</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Price: ₹3,810/sq ft average (cheaper entry)</li>\n      <li>Key driver: Naya Raipur, Smart City, state capital</li>\n      <li>Rental yield: Up to 7.1%</li>\n      <li>Appreciation: 14% stable, select areas 60-164%</li>\n      <li>Strength: State administrative centre, industrial base</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Head-to-Head</h3>\n    <p>Nagpur has a slight edge in infrastructure diversity — MIHAN is a world-class project. But Raipur offers: lower entry price + higher rental yields + similar growth trajectory. If budget is ₹40-60 lakh — Raipur gives more sq footage and better yield. If budget is ₹60L+ and want established infra — Nagpur is strong pick.</p>\n    <p><strong>Both are good 2026 investments. Raipur wins on value. Nagpur wins on infrastructure certainty.</strong></p>",
      "content_text": "Dono Central India ke major Tier-2 cities. Dono infrastructure-backed. Dono affordable vs metros. Lekin ek investor ke liye kaun better choice hai 2026 mein? Nagpur Snapshot Price: ₹4,500-7,000/sq ft Key driver: MIHAN (Multi-modal International Cargo Hub and Airport) Metro expansion: Phase 2 underway Appreciation: ~12% in 3 years Strength: Logistics, IT parks, manufacturing — diversified economy Raipur Snapshot Price: ₹3,810/sq ft average (cheaper entry) Key driver: Naya Raipur, Smart City, state capital Rental yield: Up to 7.1% Appreciation: 14% stable, select areas 60-164% Strength: State administrative centre, industrial base Head-to-Head Nagpur has a slight edge in infrastructure diversity — MIHAN is a world-class project. But Raipur offers: lower entry price + higher rental yields + similar growth trajectory. If budget is ₹40-60 lakh — Raipur gives more sq footage and better yield. If budget is ₹60L+ and want established infra — Nagpur is strong pick. Both are good 2026 investments. Raipur wins on value. Nagpur wins on infrastructure certainty.",
