      "content_html": "<p>Numbers jhooth nahi bolte. Raipur ke property prices ka honest trend analysis — past, present aur future projection.</p>\n    <h3>Past Trend (2020-2025)</h3>\n    <p>Raipur mein overall 14% appreciation in 3 years — national Tier-2 average se kam. But yeh deceptive hai. Top localities mein: Boria Kalan +164%, Sejbahar +66.7%, Abhanpur +60%. City average ko periphery affordable areas neeche kheench rahi hain.</p>\n    <h3>Current Price Snapshot (2026)</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Average new construction: ₹3,810/sq ft</li>\n      <li>Affordable areas (Abhanpur, Mandir Hasaud): ₹600-1,300/sq ft</li>\n      <li>Prime areas (VIP Road, Shankar Nagar): ₹5,000-7,000/sq ft</li>\n      <li>2BHK flats: ₹35-45 lakh range</li>\n      <li>3BHK flats: ₹55-85 lakh range</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Price Drivers Going Forward</h3>\n    <p>Naya Raipur maturity, IT park development, industrial growth, inter-state investor interest, and limited Grade-A supply in prime areas — these will drive the next appreciation wave.</p>\n    <h3>Projection (2026-2029)</h3>\n    <p>Conservative estimate: 10-15% CAGR in established areas. Optimistic (if infrastructure delivers): 20-30% in Naya Raipur corridor. This makes Raipur one of the most compelling risk-adjusted bets in Central India.</p>",
      "content_text": "Numbers jhooth nahi bolte. Raipur ke property prices ka honest trend analysis — past, present aur future projection. Past Trend (2020-2025) Raipur mein overall 14% appreciation in 3 years — national Tier-2 average se kam. But yeh deceptive hai. Top localities mein: Boria Kalan +164%, Sejbahar +66.7%, Abhanpur +60%. City average ko periphery affordable areas neeche kheench rahi hain. Current Price Snapshot (2026) Average new construction: ₹3,810/sq ft Affordable areas (Abhanpur, Mandir Hasaud): ₹600-1,300/sq ft Prime areas (VIP Road, Shankar Nagar): ₹5,000-7,000/sq ft 2BHK flats: ₹35-45 lakh range 3BHK flats: ₹55-85 lakh range Price Drivers Going Forward Naya Raipur maturity, IT park development, industrial growth, inter-state investor interest, and limited Grade-A supply in prime areas — these will drive the next appreciation wave. Projection (2026-2029) Conservative estimate: 10-15% CAGR in established areas. Optimistic (if infrastructure delivers): 20-30% in Naya Raipur corridor. This makes Raipur one of the most compelling risk-adjusted bets in Central India.",
