      "description": "Property khareedne ke baad kitni rent milegi? Yeh practical sawaal har investor ke dimag mein hota hai. Raipur ke rental market ka honest breakdown. Rental Yields by Area Amanaka: 7.1% — highest in ci...",
      "content_html": "<p>Property khareedne ke baad kitni rent milegi? Yeh practical sawaal har investor ke dimag mein hota hai. Raipur ke rental market ka honest breakdown.</p>\n    <h3>Rental Yields by Area</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Amanaka:</strong> 7.1% — highest in city</li>\n      <li><strong>VIP Road:</strong> 5.2%</li>\n      <li><strong>Mahaveer Nagar:</strong> 4.6%</li>\n      <li><strong>Avanti Vihar:</strong> 4.6%</li>\n      <li><strong>Saddu:</strong> 4.4%</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Monthly Rental Numbers (Approx)</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>1BHK (600-700 sq ft): ₹8,000-12,000/month</li>\n      <li>2BHK (950-1,200 sq ft): ₹14,000-22,000/month</li>\n      <li>3BHK (1,400-1,800 sq ft): ₹22,000-35,000/month</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Who is Renting in Raipur</h3>\n    <p>Government employees, corporate professionals, students (near colleges), families relocating for work, NRIs renting for parents — diverse, stable rental demand. Industrial growth bringing steady professional influx.</p>\n    <h3>Rental Trend</h3>\n    <p>Pan-India rents projected to rise 6-8% in 2026. Raipur, being an undersupplied premium rental market, could see higher growth in prime corridors.</p>\n    <p><strong>ROI Math:</strong> ₹40L property in Amanaka giving 7.1% yield = ₹2,84,000/year rental income = ₹23,667/month. Plus annual appreciation. That's a serious return profile.</p>",
      "content_text": "Property khareedne ke baad kitni rent milegi? Yeh practical sawaal har investor ke dimag mein hota hai. Raipur ke rental market ka honest breakdown. Rental Yields by Area Amanaka: 7.1% — highest in city VIP Road: 5.2% Mahaveer Nagar: 4.6% Avanti Vihar: 4.6% Saddu: 4.4% Monthly Rental Numbers (Approx) 1BHK (600-700 sq ft): ₹8,000-12,000/month 2BHK (950-1,200 sq ft): ₹14,000-22,000/month 3BHK (1,400-1,800 sq ft): ₹22,000-35,000/month Who is Renting in Raipur Government employees, corporate professionals, students (near colleges), families relocating for work, NRIs renting for parents — diverse, stable rental demand. Industrial growth bringing steady professional influx. Rental Trend Pan-India rents projected to rise 6-8% in 2026. Raipur, being an undersupplied premium rental market, could see higher growth in prime corridors. ROI Math: ₹40L property in Amanaka giving 7.1% yield = ₹2,84,000/year rental income = ₹23,667/month. Plus annual appreciation. That's a serious return profile.",
