      "description": "Raipur mein property koi khareed raha hai? Ek broker ya investor ke liye yeh samajhna critical hai — kyunki sahi buyer ke liye sahi pitch hoti hai. Buyer Type 1: Government Employee Largest segment. S...",
      "content_html": "<p>Raipur mein property koi khareed raha hai? Ek broker ya investor ke liye yeh samajhna critical hai — kyunki sahi buyer ke liye sahi pitch hoti hai.</p>\n    <h3>Buyer Type 1: Government Employee</h3>\n    <p>Largest segment. Stable income, conservative risk appetite. End-use dominant. Prefer established areas, clear RERA compliance, builder with track record. Budget: ₹30-60 lakh.</p>\n    <h3>Buyer Type 2: Industrial Professional</h3>\n    <p>Steel, cement, power sector workers. Transferred from other states. Looking for quality housing near work. Budget: ₹40-80 lakh. Amenity-focused.</p>\n    <h3>Buyer Type 3: Local Investor</h3>\n    <p>Business family, existing property owner, looking to expand portfolio. Plot and land preference. Budget: ₹20-1 crore. Long-term hold mentality.</p>\n    <h3>Buyer Type 4: Out-of-State Investor</h3>\n    <p>From Odisha, Jharkhand, MP — seeing Raipur value. Investment-only, not end-use. Yield-focused. Budget: ₹30-70 lakh. RERA compliance very important for this segment.</p>\n    <h3>Buyer Type 5: NRI</h3>\n    <p>Chhattisgarh roots. Looking for ancestral city investment or retirement home. Luxury segment entry. Budget: ₹75L-2Cr. Quality and brand of developer matters most.</p>\n    <h3>Broker Insight</h3>\n    <p>Identify buyer type first, then customize your pitch completely. Government employee ko yield pitch mat karo — security aur builder credibility pitch karo. Investor ko location data aur appreciation timeline chahiye.</p>",
