      "description": "Real estate sirf ameer logo ka khel nahi hai. ₹10 lakh mein bhi start ho sakta hai — agar sahi raasta pata ho. Yeh hain options. Option 1: Plotted Scheme Installment Many RERA-registered plotted schem...",
      "content_html": "<p>Real estate sirf ameer logo ka khel nahi hai. ₹10 lakh mein bhi start ho sakta hai — agar sahi raasta pata ho. Yeh hain options.</p>\n    <h3>Option 1: Plotted Scheme Installment</h3>\n    <p>Many RERA-registered plotted schemes mein ₹5-8 lakh down payment aur baaki installments mein. Total ₹15-25 lakh plots — entry ₹10L se ho sakti hai. Raipur ke fringe areas mein yeh possible hai.</p>\n    <h3>Option 2: SM-REITs</h3>\n    <p>Small and Medium REITs — new SEBI-approved instrument. ₹10 lakh minimum investment. Commercial real estate mein fractional ownership. Rental yield quarterly milta hai.</p>\n    <h3>Option 3: Real Estate Crowdfunding/Fractional</h3>\n    <p>Platforms jo ₹5-10 lakh mein commercial property mein fractional ownership dete hain. Returns: 8-12% annually projected. Liquidity: platform exit options.</p>\n    <h3>Option 4: Home Loan Leverage</h3>\n    <p>₹10L down payment par ₹40-50L property. ₹50L property = ₹40L loan at 7% = ₹31,000 EMI. If rental income ₹18,000+ hai, gap manageable hai. Long-term appreciation covers rest.</p>\n    <h3>What to Avoid at ₹10L</h3>\n    <p>Avoid unregistered plots, verbal agreements, agricultural land without NA conversion. Risk management at low capital is paramount.</p>\n    <p><strong>Best 2026 path for ₹10L starter:</strong> Down payment on RERA-registered plotted scheme in Raipur/Nagpur emerging areas. Hold 5-7 years. Compound the gain.</p>",
      "content_text": "Real estate sirf ameer logo ka khel nahi hai. ₹10 lakh mein bhi start ho sakta hai — agar sahi raasta pata ho. Yeh hain options. Option 1: Plotted Scheme Installment Many RERA-registered plotted schemes mein ₹5-8 lakh down payment aur baaki installments mein. Total ₹15-25 lakh plots — entry ₹10L se ho sakti hai. Raipur ke fringe areas mein yeh possible hai. Option 2: SM-REITs Small and Medium REITs — new SEBI-approved instrument. ₹10 lakh minimum investment. Commercial real estate mein fractional ownership. Rental yield quarterly milta hai. Option 3: Real Estate Crowdfunding/Fractional Platforms jo ₹5-10 lakh mein commercial property mein fractional ownership dete hain. Returns: 8-12% annually projected. Liquidity: platform exit options. Option 4: Home Loan Leverage ₹10L down payment par ₹40-50L property. ₹50L property = ₹40L loan at 7% = ₹31,000 EMI. If rental income ₹18,000+ hai, gap manageable hai. Long-term appreciation covers rest. What to Avoid at ₹10L Avoid unregistered plots, verbal agreements, agricultural land without NA conversion. Risk management at low capital is paramount. Best 2026 path for ₹10L starter: Down payment on RERA-registered plotted scheme in Raipur/Nagpur emerging areas. Hold 5-7 years. Compound the gain.",
