      "description": "₹50 lakh ek serious investment capital hai. Is budget mein multiple strategies possible hain — aur right choice aapko next 5-7 saal mein significant wealth create kar sakta hai. Strategy 1: Single Pro...",
      "content_html": "<p>₹50 lakh ek serious investment capital hai. Is budget mein multiple strategies possible hain — aur right choice aapko next 5-7 saal mein significant wealth create kar sakta hai.</p>\n    <h3>Strategy 1: Single Property — Best Value City</h3>\n    <p>₹50L mein Raipur: 3BHK in prime location possible. Rental yield 5-7%. Full ownership. Simple, proven strategy. Best for first-time real estate investor.</p>\n    <h3>Strategy 2: Split Investment — 2 Cities</h3>\n    <p>₹25L Raipur (residential yield play) + ₹25L Nagpur (MIHAN appreciation play). Diversification reduces concentration risk. Both growth markets 2026-2029.</p>\n    <h3>Strategy 3: Land + Liquid</h3>\n    <p>₹35L plot in Naya Raipur corridor + ₹15L in SM-REIT/MF. Plot for long-term appreciation. REIT for quarterly income. Balanced approach.</p>\n    <h3>Strategy 4: Leverage Play</h3>\n    <p>₹50L as 40% down on ₹1.25 Cr property. Home loan ₹75L at 7%. EMI ~₹58,000. Rental income ₹25,000-30,000. Net carry ₹28-33K/month. But appreciation on full ₹1.25 Cr — leverage amplifies returns.</p>\n    <h3>Which is Best?</h3>\n    <p>Strategy 1 for simplicity. Strategy 3 for income + growth balance. Strategy 4 only if income supports EMI gap. Strategy 2 for risk diversification.</p>\n    <p><strong>₹50L deployed right in 2026 = ₹1.2-1.8 Cr potential value by 2031-2032. That's real wealth creation.</strong></p>",
      "content_text": "₹50 lakh ek serious investment capital hai. Is budget mein multiple strategies possible hain — aur right choice aapko next 5-7 saal mein significant wealth create kar sakta hai. Strategy 1: Single Property — Best Value City ₹50L mein Raipur: 3BHK in prime location possible. Rental yield 5-7%. Full ownership. Simple, proven strategy. Best for first-time real estate investor. Strategy 2: Split Investment — 2 Cities ₹25L Raipur (residential yield play) + ₹25L Nagpur (MIHAN appreciation play). Diversification reduces concentration risk. Both growth markets 2026-2029. Strategy 3: Land + Liquid ₹35L plot in Naya Raipur corridor + ₹15L in SM-REIT/MF. Plot for long-term appreciation. REIT for quarterly income. Balanced approach. Strategy 4: Leverage Play ₹50L as 40% down on ₹1.25 Cr property. Home loan ₹75L at 7%. EMI ~₹58,000. Rental income ₹25,000-30,000. Net carry ₹28-33K/month. But appreciation on full ₹1.25 Cr — leverage amplifies returns. Which is Best? Strategy 1 for simplicity. Strategy 3 for income + growth balance. Strategy 4 only if income supports EMI gap. Strategy 2 for risk diversification. ₹50L deployed right in 2026 = ₹1.2-1.8 Cr potential value by 2031-2032. That's real wealth creation.",
