      "num_label": "Blog #49",
      "title": "Smart Property Buying Strategy",
      "slug": "smart-property-buying-strategy",
      "category": "Investment & ROI",
      "tags": [
        "Buying Strategy",
        "Smart Investor"
      ],
      "description": "Smart buyers don't just buy property — they follow a system. Yeh woh strategy hai jo experienced investors real estate mein consistently apply karte hain. The DRIVE Framework D — Demand: Is area mein ...",
      "content_html": "<p>Smart buyers don't just buy property — they follow a system. Yeh woh strategy hai jo experienced investors real estate mein consistently apply karte hain.</p>\n    <h3>The DRIVE Framework</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>D — Demand:</strong> Is area mein genuine demand hai? Employment? Population growth? Infrastructure?</li>\n      <li><strong>R — Return:</strong> Rental yield kitna? Appreciation potential realistic kya hai?</li>\n      <li><strong>I — Infrastructure:</strong> Kya koi confirmed government project area ke paas hai?</li>\n      <li><strong>V — Verified:</strong> RERA registered? Developer delivered before? Legal clear?</li>\n      <li><strong>E — Exit:</strong> Kaise aur kab exit karunga? Who will buy from me?</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Negotiation Tactics</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Always ask for 5-10% discount — worst case developer says no</li>\n      <li>End of quarter deals — developers under pressure to show bookings</li>\n      <li>Cash ready (loan approved) = stronger negotiating position</li>\n      <li>Compare 3 similar properties before finalizing</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Due Diligence Checklist</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>RERA verified ✓</li>\n      <li>Title search done ✓</li>\n      <li>Agreement reviewed by lawyer ✓</li>\n      <li>Nearby infrastructure projects confirmed ✓</li>\n      <li>Rental market demand verified locally ✓</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Smart buying isn't about finding the cheapest property. It's about finding the most underpriced quality — and that requires research, patience, and process.</strong></p>",
      "content_text": "Smart buyers don't just buy property — they follow a system. Yeh woh strategy hai jo experienced investors real estate mein consistently apply karte hain. The DRIVE Framework D — Demand: Is area mein genuine demand hai? Employment? Population growth? Infrastructure? R — Return: Rental yield kitna? Appreciation potential realistic kya hai? I — Infrastructure: Kya koi confirmed government project area ke paas hai? V — Verified: RERA registered? Developer delivered before? Legal clear? E — Exit: Kaise aur kab exit karunga? Who will buy from me? Negotiation Tactics Always ask for 5-10% discount — worst case developer says no End of quarter deals — developers under pressure to show bookings Cash ready (loan approved) = stronger negotiating position Compare 3 similar properties before finalizing Due Diligence Checklist RERA verified ✓ Title search done ✓ Agreement reviewed by lawyer ✓ Nearby infrastructure projects confirmed ✓ Rental market demand verified locally ✓ Smart buying isn't about finding the cheapest property. It's about finding the most underpriced quality — and that requires research, patience, and process.",
