      "description": "Real estate wealth banane mein sab se badi obstacle hain — khud ke mistakes. Yeh 5 mistakes har baar repeat hoti hain. Inhe avoid karo aur aage niklo. Mistake 1: Emotional Buying \"Relative ka project ...",
      "content_html": "<p>Real estate wealth banane mein sab se badi obstacle hain — khud ke mistakes. Yeh 5 mistakes har baar repeat hoti hain. Inhe avoid karo aur aage niklo.</p>\n    <h3>Mistake 1: Emotional Buying</h3>\n    <p>\"Relative ka project hai,\" \"Agent bahut confident tha,\" \"Vastu perfect hai.\" Emotion, data ko nahi kat sakta. Numbers first. Feeling second.</p>\n    <h3>Mistake 2: Skipping Legal Due Diligence</h3>\n    <p>₹500 stamp paper par deal karna. Lawyer se title verify na karana. RERA check na karna. Yeh ₹5,000 ki saving, ₹50 lakh ka risk hai.</p>\n    <h3>Mistake 3: Over-leveraging</h3>\n    <p>Itna bada loan jo EMI income ka 60%+ le le. One income shock — job loss, medical — aur property default. EMI ka 40% rule follow karo.</p>\n    <h3>Mistake 4: Wrong City, Right Reasoning</h3>\n    <p>\"Mumbai mein property — safe hai.\" Safe nahi hai at 2-3% yield and possible correction. Wrong city = low yield + high risk. Data se decide karo, brand se nahi.</p>\n    <h3>Mistake 5: Panic Exit</h3>\n    <p>Market thoda dip kiya — log bech dete hain. 2020 mein jo bech ke gaye, woh 2023 ka 40% appreciation chook gaye. Real estate mein patience = profit. Panic = loss.</p>\n    <h3>Bonus Mistake: Not Starting</h3>\n    <p>Sab se badi mistake — \"abhi nahi, baad mein dekhenge.\" Baad mein prices zyada hogi. EMI zyada hogi. Entry harder hogi. Aaj ka din sabse sasta din hai.</p>",
      "content_text": "Real estate wealth banane mein sab se badi obstacle hain — khud ke mistakes. Yeh 5 mistakes har baar repeat hoti hain. Inhe avoid karo aur aage niklo. Mistake 1: Emotional Buying \"Relative ka project hai,\" \"Agent bahut confident tha,\" \"Vastu perfect hai.\" Emotion, data ko nahi kat sakta. Numbers first. Feeling second. Mistake 2: Skipping Legal Due Diligence ₹500 stamp paper par deal karna. Lawyer se title verify na karana. RERA check na karna. Yeh ₹5,000 ki saving, ₹50 lakh ka risk hai. Mistake 3: Over-leveraging Itna bada loan jo EMI income ka 60%+ le le. One income shock — job loss, medical — aur property default. EMI ka 40% rule follow karo. Mistake 4: Wrong City, Right Reasoning \"Mumbai mein property — safe hai.\" Safe nahi hai at 2-3% yield and possible correction. Wrong city = low yield + high risk. Data se decide karo, brand se nahi. Mistake 5: Panic Exit Market thoda dip kiya — log bech dete hain. 2020 mein jo bech ke gaye, woh 2023 ka 40% appreciation chook gaye. Real estate mein patience = profit. Panic = loss. Bonus Mistake: Not Starting Sab se badi mistake — \"abhi nahi, baad mein dekhenge.\" Baad mein prices zyada hogi. EMI zyada hogi. Entry harder hogi. Aaj ka din sabse sasta din hai.",
