      "description": "India mein women real estate investors ka segment tezi se badh raha hai. Government bhi incentives deti hai. Ek dedicated guide women investors ke liye. Government Benefits for Women Property Buyers S...",
      "content_html": "<p>India mein women real estate investors ka segment tezi se badh raha hai. Government bhi incentives deti hai. Ek dedicated guide women investors ke liye.</p>\n    <h3>Government Benefits for Women Property Buyers</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Stamp duty: 1-2% discount in many states (including Chhattisgarh)</li>\n      <li>PM Awas Yojana: Priority if property in woman's name</li>\n      <li>PMAY credit-linked subsidy: Higher eligibility if co-borrower/owner woman</li>\n      <li>Some state governments give additional income tax benefits</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Home Loan Advantages</h3>\n    <p>Many banks offer 0.05% to 0.10% lower interest rate for women primary borrowers. On ₹40L loan, 0.10% = ₹800/month saving = ₹1.92L over 20 years.</p>\n    <h3>Investment Mindset</h3>\n    <p>Research shows women investors tend to make more patient, research-based real estate decisions — which historically outperform emotional, reactive decisions. This is a natural advantage.</p>\n    <h3>Starting Points for Women Investors in 2026</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Start with one RERA-verified flat — preferably in your name for maximum benefits</li>\n      <li>Joint loan with spouse if needed for higher eligibility</li>\n      <li>Tier-2 cities for better yield + affordability</li>\n      <li>Consult a financial advisor for tax planning around property income</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Women investors — government aapke saath hai, market aapke favour mein hai, aur data kehta hai aap better long-term decisions lete hain. Time to invest.</strong></p>",
