      "description": "Ek property = good start. Real wealth = portfolio. Kaise build karein ek systematic real estate portfolio jo financial freedom de? Phase 1: Foundation (Property 1) RERA-verified, mid-segment, high-yie...",
      "content_html": "<p>Ek property = good start. Real wealth = portfolio. Kaise build karein ek systematic real estate portfolio jo financial freedom de?</p>\n    <h3>Phase 1: Foundation (Property 1)</h3>\n    <p>RERA-verified, mid-segment, high-yield Tier-2 property. Goal: Learn the process. Generate first rental income. Build credit history. Budget: Whatever you can manage. Raipur/Nagpur — ideal starting point.</p>\n    <h3>Phase 2: Leverage (Property 2-3)</h3>\n    <p>Use appreciated equity from property 1 as partial collateral/confidence for loan on property 2. Or save rental income as down payment. Choose different micro-market for diversification. Timeline: 3-5 years after property 1.</p>\n    <h3>Phase 3: Diversification (Property 3-5)</h3>\n    <p>Mix: 1 commercial, 1-2 residential. Consider different city. Balance yield-heavy properties with appreciation-heavy plots. Include SM-REIT for liquidity cushion.</p>\n    <h3>Phase 4: Professional Management</h3>\n    <p>At 3+ properties — hire property management company. Focus shifts from management to strategic acquisition. Your time becomes more valuable than micro-management.</p>\n    <h3>Portfolio Health Metrics</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Average yield across portfolio: Target 5%+</li>\n      <li>LTV (loan-to-value): Keep below 60%</li>\n      <li>Geographic concentration: Max 60% in one city</li>\n      <li>Liquidity buffer: 6-month EMI coverage in liquid assets</li>\n    </ul>",
      "content_text": "Ek property = good start. Real wealth = portfolio. Kaise build karein ek systematic real estate portfolio jo financial freedom de? Phase 1: Foundation (Property 1) RERA-verified, mid-segment, high-yield Tier-2 property. Goal: Learn the process. Generate first rental income. Build credit history. Budget: Whatever you can manage. Raipur/Nagpur — ideal starting point. Phase 2: Leverage (Property 2-3) Use appreciated equity from property 1 as partial collateral/confidence for loan on property 2. Or save rental income as down payment. Choose different micro-market for diversification. Timeline: 3-5 years after property 1. Phase 3: Diversification (Property 3-5) Mix: 1 commercial, 1-2 residential. Consider different city. Balance yield-heavy properties with appreciation-heavy plots. Include SM-REIT for liquidity cushion. Phase 4: Professional Management At 3+ properties — hire property management company. Focus shifts from management to strategic acquisition. Your time becomes more valuable than micro-management. Portfolio Health Metrics Average yield across portfolio: Target 5%+ LTV (loan-to-value): Keep below 60% Geographic concentration: Max 60% in one city Liquidity buffer: 6-month EMI coverage in liquid assets",
