      "description": "Ek broker aur ek real estate business owner mein fark kya hai? Broker akela kaam karta hai — deal se deal. Business owner ek system banata hai jo uske bina bhi chal sakta hai. Yeh transition kaise hot...",
      "content_html": "<p>Ek broker aur ek real estate business owner mein fark kya hai? Broker akela kaam karta hai — deal se deal. Business owner ek system banata hai jo uske bina bhi chal sakta hai. Yeh transition kaise hoti hai?</p>\n    <h3>Broker Mindset vs Business Mindset</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Broker:</strong> \"Mujhe aaj deal chahiye.\" <strong>Business:</strong> \"Mujhe pipeline chahiye jo 6 months mein deals de.\"</li>\n      <li><strong>Broker:</strong> Khud sab karta hai. <strong>Business:</strong> Team, systems, processes build karta hai.</li>\n      <li><strong>Broker:</strong> Commission income. <strong>Business:</strong> Scalable revenue + team commission cut.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>3 Steps to Make the Shift</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Step 1 — Specialize:</strong> 1-2 cities, 1-2 property types. Expert bano, generalist nahi. Clients trust experts more.</li>\n      <li><strong>Step 2 — Build Lead System:</strong> Not dependent on any one source. Digital ads + referrals + walk-ins + network = diversified pipeline.</li>\n      <li><strong>Step 3 — Hire Support:</strong> First hire: admin who handles paperwork and follow-ups. Frees you for client meetings and deal closures.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Revenue Model Shift</h3>\n    <p>Solo broker: Your income = your deals. Business: Team deals generate you 20-30% override. 10 agents doing ₹2L commission each = ₹20L. Your override: ₹4-6L. That's business income.</p>\n    <p><strong>The shift happens in mind first, then in market. Decide you're building a business — not just closing deals. Everything else follows.</strong></p>",
      "content_text": "Ek broker aur ek real estate business owner mein fark kya hai? Broker akela kaam karta hai — deal se deal. Business owner ek system banata hai jo uske bina bhi chal sakta hai. Yeh transition kaise hoti hai? Broker Mindset vs Business Mindset Broker: \"Mujhe aaj deal chahiye.\" Business: \"Mujhe pipeline chahiye jo 6 months mein deals de.\" Broker: Khud sab karta hai. Business: Team, systems, processes build karta hai. Broker: Commission income. Business: Scalable revenue + team commission cut. 3 Steps to Make the Shift Step 1 — Specialize: 1-2 cities, 1-2 property types. Expert bano, generalist nahi. Clients trust experts more. Step 2 — Build Lead System: Not dependent on any one source. Digital ads + referrals + walk-ins + network = diversified pipeline. Step 3 — Hire Support: First hire: admin who handles paperwork and follow-ups. Frees you for client meetings and deal closures. Revenue Model Shift Solo broker: Your income = your deals. Business: Team deals generate you 20-30% override. 10 agents doing ₹2L commission each = ₹20L. Your override: ₹4-6L. That's business income. The shift happens in mind first, then in market. Decide you're building a business — not just closing deals. Everything else follows.",
