      "description": "Data driven investing — yeh term suna hai. Lekin real estate mein practically data kahan se aata hai aur kaise use hota hai? Practical guide. Key Data Sources for Real Estate Investors in India 99acre...",
      "content_html": "<p>Data driven investing — yeh term suna hai. Lekin real estate mein practically data kahan se aata hai aur kaise use hota hai? Practical guide.</p>\n    <h3>Key Data Sources for Real Estate Investors in India</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>99acres / MagicBricks / Housing.com:</strong> Listing prices, price trends, demand heatmaps</li>\n      <li><strong>PropEquity / NoBroker data:</strong> Transaction data, rental yields, project-level data</li>\n      <li><strong>RBI RESIDEX:</strong> Official house price index by city — quarterly updates</li>\n      <li><strong>CREDAI / Anarock Reports:</strong> Industry level supply, demand, absorption data</li>\n      <li><strong>Registrar office data:</strong> Actual transaction prices (not listing) — ground truth</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>How to Use Each Data Point</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Price trend (3 yr):</strong> Momentum indicator. Consistent up = healthy market. Volatile = risky.</li>\n      <li><strong>Rental yield:</strong> Passive income check. 5%+ = viable. Below 3% = value trap.</li>\n      <li><strong>Absorption rate:</strong> How fast new units are being bought. High absorption = strong demand. Low = supply excess.</li>\n      <li><strong>Unsold inventory months:</strong> <12 months = healthy. 18+ months = oversupplied market.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Data Doesn't Lie — But It Can Be Misread</h3>\n    <p>Average city price can hide micro-market extremes. Always ask: What's the standard deviation? Who are the outliers? Why are they outliers? The insight is in the deviation, not the average.</p>\n    <p><strong>Data + local knowledge + physical visit = the complete investment intelligence picture. Data alone is half the story.</strong></p>",
      "content_text": "Data driven investing — yeh term suna hai. Lekin real estate mein practically data kahan se aata hai aur kaise use hota hai? Practical guide. Key Data Sources for Real Estate Investors in India 99acres / MagicBricks / Housing.com: Listing prices, price trends, demand heatmaps PropEquity / NoBroker data: Transaction data, rental yields, project-level data RBI RESIDEX: Official house price index by city — quarterly updates CREDAI / Anarock Reports: Industry level supply, demand, absorption data Registrar office data: Actual transaction prices (not listing) — ground truth How to Use Each Data Point Price trend (3 yr): Momentum indicator. Consistent up = healthy market. Volatile = risky. Rental yield: Passive income check. 5%+ = viable. Below 3% = value trap. Absorption rate: How fast new units are being bought. High absorption = strong demand. Low = supply excess. Unsold inventory months: Data Doesn't Lie — But It Can Be Misread Average city price can hide micro-market extremes. Always ask: What's the standard deviation? Who are the outliers? Why are they outliers? The insight is in the deviation, not the average. Data + local knowledge + physical visit = the complete investment intelligence picture. Data alone is half the story.",
