      "description": "Investors ke liye: understand karo kause log property khareed rahe hain — market ko predict kar sakte ho. Brokers ke liye: understand karo apna buyer — deal close kar sakte ho. India's Property Buyer ...",
      "content_html": "<p>Investors ke liye: understand karo kause log property khareed rahe hain — market ko predict kar sakte ho. Brokers ke liye: understand karo apna buyer — deal close kar sakte ho.</p>\n    <h3>India's Property Buyer Segments 2026</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>First-time Home Buyer (35% of market):</strong> 28-38 years, dual income, EMI-sensitive, lifestyle-focused. Drivers: Marriage, baby, work stability. Price sensitivity: High.</li>\n      <li><strong>Upgrade Buyer (25%):</strong> 38-50 years, existing property owner, looking for larger/better. Motivated by life stage + portfolio upgrade. Less price sensitive.</li>\n      <li><strong>Investor-only Buyer (25%):</strong> Any age, return-focused, data-driven. Motivated by yield + appreciation. Very price sensitive on entry.</li>\n      <li><strong>NRI Buyer (10%):</strong> Overseas income, property in India for roots/retirement. Dollar advantage. Emotional + financial drivers combined. Less negotiation, more trust-seeking.</li>\n      <li><strong>Corporate/HNI (5%):</strong> Multiple properties, portfolio thinking, advisor-driven.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>Post-COVID Behavioral Shifts</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Space premium — bigger homes even if farther from work</li>\n      <li>Amenity focus — gym, pool, green space non-negotiable</li>\n      <li>Digital first — most research online before any site visit</li>\n      <li>Green/sustainable building interest growing</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>What This Means for Brokers</h3>\n    <p>Identify buyer segment before pitching. First-timer needs hand-holding and emotional reassurance. Investor needs ROI numbers and data. NRI needs trust and remote management solution. Same property, completely different pitch.</p>",
      "content_text": "Investors ke liye: understand karo kause log property khareed rahe hain — market ko predict kar sakte ho. Brokers ke liye: understand karo apna buyer — deal close kar sakte ho. India's Property Buyer Segments 2026 First-time Home Buyer (35% of market): 28-38 years, dual income, EMI-sensitive, lifestyle-focused. Drivers: Marriage, baby, work stability. Price sensitivity: High. Upgrade Buyer (25%): 38-50 years, existing property owner, looking for larger/better. Motivated by life stage + portfolio upgrade. Less price sensitive. Investor-only Buyer (25%): Any age, return-focused, data-driven. Motivated by yield + appreciation. Very price sensitive on entry. NRI Buyer (10%): Overseas income, property in India for roots/retirement. Dollar advantage. Emotional + financial drivers combined. Less negotiation, more trust-seeking. Corporate/HNI (5%): Multiple properties, portfolio thinking, advisor-driven. Post-COVID Behavioral Shifts Space premium — bigger homes even if farther from work Amenity focus — gym, pool, green space non-negotiable Digital first — most research online before any site visit Green/sustainable building interest growing What This Means for Brokers Identify buyer segment before pitching. First-timer needs hand-holding and emotional reassurance. Investor needs ROI numbers and data. NRI needs trust and remote management solution. Same property, completely different pitch.",
